# Delivery standards

Any implementation work in this repo must follow `.cursor/skills/delivery-standards/SKILL.md` (also `.claude/skills/delivery-standards/SKILL.md`).

## Required on every code change

1. **TDD-first** — failing test(s) before implementation for `/engine`, `/db`, agents, IPC, and other testable logic.
2. **Verify before done** — all must pass; do not report completion otherwise:
   - `npm test`
   - `npm run lint`
   - `npm run build`
   - `npm run deadcode` (ts-prune vs `.tsprune-ignore`; if export moves/deletes drift the baseline, run `npm run deadcode:refresh` after confirming the new findings are intentional)
   - **`act` CI** — run `.github/workflows/pr-checks.yml` and `.github/workflows/deadcode.yml` via `act` (see `act-ci-after-local-tasks` rule). If Docker is not running, **pause and ask the user to start Docker** — do not silently skip or fall back.
3. **Board traceability** — **ALWAYS write a ticket yourself.** Never ask the user whether to create one, which number to use, or whether to skip tracking. Create `/board/backlog/` (or move to `in-progress` when starting) with Description + checkable Acceptance Criteria before or as you start. If the user named a ticket id, use `complete-ticket` skill. Next free id: look at highest `NNN` under `board/` and increment.

## Also required

- Read `README.md` for architecture boundaries.
- Check off acceptance criteria only after verification; move tickets to `done/` when complete.
- Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Campaign create pipeline changes:** follow `docs/runbooks/campaign-create-change-checklist.md`.

## Exceptions

- Read-only answers with no code changes: no ticket or test gate required.
- Never treat “tiny fix” / CI fluff as an excuse to skip a ticket or to ask the user first.
